---
// src/pages/civil/cee335l/day9.astro
const title = "Day 9 — Practice: Building Frame";
const description = "Practice session for the multi-story building frame. Apply full load combinations, check member forces, and start design verification.";
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>{title} | CEE335L | Mathify</title>
  <meta name="description" content={description} />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Mono:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Playfair+Display:wght@700;900&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <style>
    :root{--bg:#0d0d0f;--bg2:#13131a;--border:#2a2a3a;--text:#e8e8f0;--muted:#7a7a9a;--accent:#f0a500;--accent2:#3ecfcf;--accent3:#e05c5c;--green:#4ade80;--mono:'Space Mono',monospace;--serif:'Playfair Display',serif;--sans:'Inter',sans-serif;}
    *,*::before,*::after{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0;}html{scroll-behavior:smooth;}body{background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);font-family:var(--sans);font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;overflow-x:hidden;}
    nav{position:sticky;top:0;z-index:100;background:rgba(13,13,15,.92);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding:.75rem 2rem;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:2rem;}
    .nav-logo{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:1rem;color:var(--accent);text-decoration:none;}
    .nav-links{display:flex;gap:1.5rem;list-style:none;}
    .nav-links a{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.75rem;color:var(--muted);text-decoration:none;letter-spacing:.05em;transition:color .2s;}
    .nav-links a:hover{color:var(--text);}
    .breadcrumb{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.7rem;color:var(--muted);margin-left:auto;letter-spacing:.08em;}
    .breadcrumb a{color:var(--muted);text-decoration:none;}.breadcrumb a:hover{color:var(--accent);}
    .hero{padding:4rem 2rem 3rem;max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);}
    .day-tag{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.68rem;color:var(--accent);letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.5rem;margin-bottom:.75rem;}
    .day-tag::before{content:'';width:2rem;height:1px;background:var(--accent);}
    .hero h1{font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(1.8rem,4vw,2.8rem);font-weight:900;line-height:1.15;margin-bottom:.75rem;}
    .hero h1 span{color:var(--accent);}
    .hero-sub{font-size:1rem;color:var(--muted);max-width:580px;margin-bottom:1.5rem;}
    .badge-row{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:.6rem;}
    .badge{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.68rem;letter-spacing:.06em;padding:.28rem .7rem;border-radius:4px;border:1px solid;}
    .badge-amber{color:var(--accent);border-color:var(--accent);background:rgba(240,165,0,.08);}
    .badge-teal{color:var(--accent2);border-color:var(--accent2);background:rgba(62,207,207,.08);}
    .badge-green{color:var(--green);border-color:var(--green);background:rgba(74,222,128,.08);}
    .section{max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:3.5rem 2rem;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);}
    .section-num{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.65rem;color:var(--accent);letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.75rem;margin-bottom:.75rem;}
    .section-num::after{content:'';flex:0 0 3rem;height:1px;background:var(--border);}
    .section h2{font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(1.3rem,3vw,1.9rem);font-weight:700;margin-bottom:.5rem;}
    .section-intro{color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:2rem;max-width:620px;}
    .coming-soon{background:var(--bg2);border:1px dashed var(--border);border-radius:10px;padding:2rem;text-align:center;color:var(--muted);font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.8rem;}
    .coming-soon strong{color:var(--accent);display:block;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:.5rem;}
    .checklist{list-style:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:.75rem;}
    .checklist li{background:var(--bg2);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:.9rem 1.25rem;display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:.75rem;font-size:.88rem;}
    .checklist li::before{content:'☐';font-family:var(--mono);font-size:1rem;color:var(--accent);flex-shrink:0;margin-top:.05rem;}
    .checklist li strong{color:var(--text);display:block;margin-bottom:.2rem;}
    .checklist li span{color:var(--muted);font-size:.82rem;}
    .day-nav{max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:2rem 2rem 3rem;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;}
    .nav-btn{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.75rem;letter-spacing:.05em;padding:.6rem 1.25rem;border-radius:6px;border:1px solid var(--border);background:var(--bg2);color:var(--muted);text-decoration:none;transition:all .2s;}
    .nav-btn:hover{border-color:var(--accent);color:var(--accent);}
    .nav-btn.next{background:rgba(240,165,0,.08);border-color:var(--accent);color:var(--accent);}
    .day-center{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.7rem;color:var(--muted);letter-spacing:.1em;}
    @media(max-width:600px){nav{padding:.75rem 1rem;}.hero,.section{padding-left:1.25rem;padding-right:1.25rem;}.day-nav{padding:1.5rem 1.25rem 2.5rem;}}
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<nav>
  <a href="/" class="nav-logo">mathify</a>
  <ul class="nav-links">
    <li><a href="/math">Math</a></li>
    <li><a href="/physics">Physics</a></li>
    <li><a href="/civil">Civil</a></li>
  </ul>
  <span class="breadcrumb">
    <a href="/civil">Civil</a> ›
    <a href="/civil/cee335l/">CEE335L</a> › Day 9
  </span>
</nav>

<header class="hero">
  <div class="day-tag">Day 9 of 11 — Class 9</div>
  <h1>Practice:<br><span>Building Frame</span></h1>
  <p class="hero-sub">
    Apply everything from Days 7–8. Work through the full building frame with gravity + wind + seismic combinations. Extract design forces for a critical beam and column.
  </p>
  <div class="badge-row">
    <span class="badge badge-amber">Practice</span>
    <span class="badge badge-teal">Full Load Combos</span>
    <span class="badge badge-teal">Design Forces</span>
    <span class="badge badge-green">Exam Prep</span>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-num">01 — Why</div>
  <h2>Practice is where the model mistakes surface</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">
    Day 9 has no new theory. Its purpose is to give you time with the model before Exam 2. Every modelling mistake you find and fix today is one less failure in the exam.
  </p>
  <div class="coming-soon">
    <strong>Content Coming Soon</strong>
    Common mistakes caught at this stage: wrong load direction, missing load combos, incorrect mass source, pinned instead of fixed base, shell element orientation errors.
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-num">02 — Concept</div>
  <h2>Reading design forces from ETABS</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">For each member, ETABS outputs: P (axial), V2, V3 (shear in two directions), T (torsion), M2, M3 (moment in two directions). For design, you need the envelope values across all load combinations.</p>
  <div class="coming-soon">
    <strong>Content Coming Soon</strong>
    How to display force envelopes. What Pu, Mu, Vu mean for RC design (factored forces). How to export a table of critical member forces.
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-num">03 — Walkthrough</div>
  <h2>Day 9 practice checklist</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">Work through this checklist on your Day 7–8 model before Day 10.</p>
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>
      <div>
        <strong>Run all load combinations</strong>
        <span>Gravity only, wind governs, seismic governs, uplift check. Confirm no analysis errors.</span>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div>
        <strong>Check story drift under wind</strong>
        <span>Display deformed shape under wind combo. Record drift at each floor. Is it within H/400?</span>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div>
        <strong>Identify critical beam (max Mu)</strong>
        <span>Display M3 diagram. Which beam has the largest factored moment? Note the span and floor level.</span>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div>
        <strong>Identify critical column (max Pu and Mu)</strong>
        <span>Ground-floor corner columns typically govern under seismic due to combined axial + moment. Check P-M interaction.</span>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div>
        <strong>Extract base reactions</strong>
        <span>Display → Show Table → Base Reactions. Record sum of FZ (should equal total building weight × gravity combo factor).</span>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div>
        <strong>Verify base shear matches BNBC calculation</strong>
        <span>Sum of horizontal base reactions under seismic combo should match V computed by hand. Tolerance: ±5%.</span>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-num">04 — Check Yourself</div>
  <h2>Exam 2 self-assessment</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">Day 10 is more practice. Day 11 is Exam 2. Test yourself now.</p>
  <div class="coming-soon">
    <strong>Exam 2 Review Quiz Coming Soon</strong>
    Topics: BNBC wind and seismic load calculation, story force distribution, load combinations (gravity + lateral), reading P-M interaction diagrams, drift check procedure, identifying critical members.
  </div>
</section>

<nav class="day-nav">
  <a href="/civil/cee335l/day8" class="nav-btn">← Day 8</a>
  <span class="day-center">CEE335L · Day 9 / 11</span>
  <a href="/civil/cee335l/day10" class="nav-btn next">Day 10 →</a>
</nav>

</body>
</html>
